<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654982>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 16. Sympagurus villosus n.sp. a, maxillu1e, internal; b, endopod of same; c, left 3rd maxilliped, internal; d, right antennal peduncle, lateral; e, left male 1st gonopod, mesial; f, left male 2nd gonopod, anterior; g,h, exopod of uropods, dorsal: g, left; h, right; i, telson. Scales = 2 mm (a,d-i d-i), 1 mm (b), and 4 mm (c). (Queensland: a-c, paratype male [SL 13.7 mm], QM W16516; d-i, holotype male [SL 13.8 mm], NTM er 010912)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4654982/files/figure.png" .

